<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861223-0069 </DOCNO><HL> Borden Plans to SellMedium-Term Notes</HL><DD> 12/23/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BNBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Borden Inc. plans to offer as much as $315 million of medium-term notes.    The notes will be offered on a continuing basis through Salomon Brothers Inc., agent for the program. They will have maturities ranging from nine months to 10 years. Terms of each transaction will be established at the time of sale.    Borden, a food and chemicals company, will use proceeds to pay commercial paper debt incurred in its acquisition of BCI Beatrice Dairy Products Inc. </TEXT></DOC>